oposal of a reprocessing moratorium may therefore be put to members once again later this year. <br>However, yesterday's debate does clearly establish that a majority of members in both houses of parliament agree with the government that there should be no arbitrary lifetime limits for existing nuclear power plants. It also shows that a majority oppose introducing an outright ban on reprocessing, as originally proposed by the government. The parliamentary debate follows publication of a recent opinion poll, which showed that well over two-thirds of the Swiss population believes the country should retain the option to reprocess spent fuel . <br>In addition, members agreed that the new law should specify in principle・that all Swiss spent fuel and radioactive waste should be disposed of domestically. However, they also voted to retain the option of final disposal outside Switzerland, in the event that a suitable・site was identified at a future date. <br><br>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br><br>First Europe, then the World. Go Nuclear! Hooray!<br><br> <br><br> <br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A> at: 6/30/02 11:14:58 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=111.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=111.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=111.topic><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></